<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-08-22T03:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-08-22T03:00:00-05:00" n="348" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d348">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">862.24/739: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in France (<persName type="from">Tuck</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Vichy</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-08-22T10:00:00+02:00">August
                                        22, 1942—10 a.m.</date>
                                    <lb/> [Received 2:20 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>1223. Department’s 507, August 17, 2 p.m. I have pressed Rochat<note n="37" xml:id="d348fn37">Charles Antoine Rochat, Secretary
                                    General of the French Foreign Office.</note> on three separate
                                occasions for a reply to our note requesting <pb facs="0368" n="362" xml:id="pg_362"/> the renewal by the French Government of the
                                assurance previously given and on the basis of which our Government
                                agreed to resume the shipment of supplies to French North
                                Africa.</p>
                            <p>Today Rochat informed me that I might expect his Government’s reply
                                at an early date probably tomorrow August 23.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Tuck</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>